  content:
    - type: text
      text: "Read @AI_PARTNER_CONTEXT.md. Currently when users submit reports and articles, we crawl the article content and return it to the frontend via API to display the article title and summary. There is a UX issue where our crawler does not always successfully return the article title. Also, the article content is in markdown format which is hard to render well on the frontend. The current plan is to run the crawled content through AI (using the Doubao model) after the crawler returns -- the AI input would be all the crawled content, we select the valid article content, then have the AI generate a title if there is not one, and simultaneously generate a summary of no more than 100 characters. These two things would be returned from the API to the frontend as a fallback for the original. Also in the article sub-session, we currently submit an article card that displays the article content by simply showing the raw markdown -- this should be replaced with the article summary we just described. You may need to add a new column in the database to store this summary. I am not sure if the current schema has it. Give me a plan. /autoresearch Iterations: 10 ultrathink"
